                     <interp inst="t17750531-2-person277" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's ten months. I went to live there the 25th of April 1774, and came away when this affair happened. I went to nurse the children. About a month after Mrs. Rudd's lying-inn, she came to me and said, tell your master for God's sake, I am going out; that Mr. Adair called for her. My master did not come in, so nothing was said: she never mentioned Mr. William Adair's name particularly to me, but has named it as her acquaintance: she sent me down to shew the children to a gentleman; who he was I don't know.</p>
